USAREUR in Germany provides over 160,000 acres of land for military training in varied terrain. The Army's mission in Germany depends on maintaining authentic training conditions through good environmental stewardship. This quick info guide contains extracts of GTA SOP #1 and #8, it is not a replacement for SOPs #1-10

- Stay out of OFF-LIMITS areas (temporary or permanent), such as forests, tree nurseries, check dams and historical sites. OFF-LIMITS are marked with red and yellow striped posts (Seibert Stakes). - Digging in non-designated areas is prohibited. - Do not enter mining shafts, natural caves, abandoned villages, building ruins and cellars, or areas where tree trunks are notably curved; this may indicate a depression or sinkhole-like structure. - Cutting of trees and branches for camouflage purposes must be coordinated with the local forestry office. Units are responsible to police area for litter, to include misfire pit. - Remove all commo, concertina, TOW and trip wire, as well as wires from guided missiles after firing. Segregate and dispose of waste in authorized containers. - Execute DECON operations only in auhtorized areas. - Report any wildlife death or injury to Range Operations.

- Obtain approval from JTF-E Joint Operations Center (JOC) prior to use of any training area. - The scheduling unit is fully responsible for proper use of the training area and must follow all policies pertaining to training facilities prescribed by JTF-E JOC. - Digging foxholes or defensive positions requires prior approval.

Use of the training areas and ranges is restricted by Municipal, Regional, and Federal Authorities. Units must adhere to the following: a. Comply with the regulations [Range SOP] and restrictions concerning the use of the training areas and firing ranges. b. Adhere to environmental/ecological requirements. c. Restore the area to near original/pre-use conditions (i.e. cover ditches, remove all garbage, etc.). d. Conduct NO operations in cultivated farm/orchard areas. e. Preserve and protect all cultivated foliage and trees. f. Prohibit the removal of any fruit. IAW Italian law, Commanders contributing to the abuse and misuse of training areas will be subject to prosecution. Upon occupying the training area, the OIC/NCOIC will minimize all possible damages and conflict with local authorities and inhabitants.
